msgid ""
"topo_affinity"
msgstr "topo_affinity"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:93
msgid ""
"`topo_affinity` is designed for devices that report NPU-to-CPU affinity "
"in `npu-smi info -t topo`, such as A2 and Atlas 300 inference products. "
"The allocator uses the affinity list to build a CPU pool for each running"
" NPU."
msgstr ""
"`topo_affinity` 专为在 `npu-smi info -t topo` 中报告 NPU 到 CPU 亲和性的设备设计，例如 A2 和 Atlas 300 推理产品。分配器使用亲和性列表为每个运行中的 NPU 构建 CPU 池。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:97
msgid "For each running NPU:"
msgstr "对于每个运行中的 NPU："

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:98
msgid ""
"Look up its affinity CPUs from `npu-smi info -t topo` (the CPU list "
"closest to the NPU)."
msgstr "从 `npu-smi info -t topo` 查找其亲和性 CPU（最接近 NPU 的 CPU 列表）。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:99
msgid ""
"Intersect with `allowed_cpus` to respect container cpusets or system "
"restrictions."
msgstr "与 `allowed_cpus` 取交集，以尊重容器 cpuset 或系统限制。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:100
msgid ""
"If the intersection yields fewer than 5 CPUs, the allocator extends the "
"pool to the next NUMA node using `lscpu -e=CPU,NODE`."
msgstr "如果交集产生的 CPU 少于 5 个，分配器使用 `lscpu -e=CPU,NODE` 将池扩展到下一个 NUMA 节点。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:101
msgid ""
"The extended pool is sorted and sliced to exactly 5 CPUs for the worker."
msgstr "扩展后的池被排序并切片为恰好 5 个 CPU 供工作进程使用。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:103
msgid ""
"This ensures that even with limited affinity, the worker gets a "
"deterministic set of CPUs for binding."
msgstr "这确保了即使在亲和性有限的情况下，工作进程也能获得一组确定性的 CPU 用于绑定。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:105
msgid "Role Assignment"
msgstr "角色分配"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:107
msgid ""
"Once the CPU pool is built, the allocator assigns specific roles to "
"individual CPUs. The assignment is deterministic and based on the sorted "
"CPU list."
msgstr "一旦 CPU 池构建完成，分配器将特定角色分配给各个 CPU。分配是确定性的，基于排序后的 CPU 列表。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:110
msgid "For devices with IRQ binding (A2, A3, Atlas 300):"
msgstr "对于支持 IRQ 绑定的设备（A2、A3、Atlas 300）："

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:111
msgid "CPU 0: main worker process"
msgstr "CPU 0：主工作进程"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:112
msgid "CPU 1: ACL thread"
msgstr "CPU 1：ACL 线程"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:113
msgid "CPU 2: release thread"
msgstr "CPU 2：释放线程"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:114
msgid "CPU 3: SQ IRQ"
msgstr "CPU 3：SQ IRQ"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:115
msgid "CPU 4: CQ IRQ"
msgstr "CPU 4：CQ IRQ"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:117
msgid "For Ascend 950 (no IRQ binding):"
msgstr "对于 Ascend 950（无 IRQ 绑定）："

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:118
msgid "CPU 0: main worker process"
msgstr "CPU 0：主工作进程"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:119
msgid "CPU 1: ACL thread"
msgstr "CPU 1：ACL 线程"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:120
msgid "CPU 2: release thread"
msgstr "CPU 2：释放线程"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:122
msgid ""
"The remaining CPUs in the pool (if any) are left unassigned and available"
" for other system processes."
msgstr "池中剩余的 CPU（如果有）保持未分配状态，可供其他系统进程使用。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:124
msgid "Binding Execution"
msgstr "绑定执行"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:126
msgid ""
"The actual binding is performed by the `CpuBinding` class, which uses "
"`os.sched_setaffinity` for thread binding and writes to "
"`/proc/irq/<irq>/smp_affinity` for IRQ binding. The binding happens "
"after the worker process is initialized but before model loading begins."
msgstr ""
"实际绑定由 `CpuBinding` 类执行，它使用 `os.sched_setaffinity` 进行线程绑定，并写入 `/proc/irq/<irq>/smp_affinity` 进行 IRQ 绑定。绑定发生在工作进程初始化之后、模型加载开始之前。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:130
msgid "The binding order is:"
msgstr "绑定顺序为："

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:131
msgid "Bind the main worker process to its assigned CPU."
msgstr "将主工作进程绑定到其分配的 CPU。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:132
msgid "Bind the ACL thread to its assigned CPU."
msgstr "将 ACL 线程绑定到其分配的 CPU。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:133
msgid "Bind the release thread to its assigned CPU."
msgstr "将释放线程绑定到其分配的 CPU。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:134
msgid "Bind SQ and CQ IRQs to their assigned CPUs (if applicable)."
msgstr "将 SQ 和 CQ IRQ 绑定到其分配的 CPU（如果适用）。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:136
msgid ""
"If any binding step fails (e.g., due to permission issues or invalid CPU "
"IDs), the error is logged but the worker continues without binding for "
"that specific role."
msgstr "如果任何绑定步骤失败（例如，由于权限问题或无效的 CPU ID），则会记录错误，但工作进程会继续运行，而不对该特定角色进行绑定。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:139
msgid "Configuration"
msgstr "配置"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:141
msgid ""
"CPU binding is enabled by default starting from vllm-ascend v0.18.0rc1. "
"It can be controlled through the following mechanisms:"
msgstr ""
"CPU 绑定从 vllm-ascend v0.18.0rc1 开始默认启用。可以通过以下机制进行控制："

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:144
msgid "`enable_cpu_binding=True` in `additional_config` (default: `True`)"
msgstr "`additional_config` 中的 `enable_cpu_binding=True`（默认值：`True`）"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:145
msgid ""
"`VLLM_ASCEND_CPU_BINDING=0` environment variable to disable at runtime"
msgstr "`VLLM_ASCEND_CPU_BINDING=0` 环境变量，用于在运行时禁用"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:146
msgid ""
"`--numa-bind` flag (converted to `enable_cpu_binding=True` internally)"
msgstr "`--numa-bind` 标志（内部转换为 `enable_cpu_binding=True`）"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:148
msgid ""
"When disabled, the worker process and threads are not bound to specific "
"CPUs, and the Linux scheduler is free to place them anywhere on the "
"system."
msgstr "禁用时，工作进程和线程不会绑定到特定 CPU，Linux 调度器可以自由地将它们放置在系统的任何位置。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:151
msgid "Troubleshooting"
msgstr "故障排除"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:153
msgid ""
"If you encounter issues with CPU binding, check the following:"
msgstr "如果遇到 CPU 绑定问题，请检查以下内容："

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:155
msgid ""
"**Permission denied**: IRQ binding requires root or `CAP_SYS_ADMIN`. Run "
"the worker with appropriate privileges or disable IRQ binding."
msgstr ""
"**权限被拒绝**：IRQ 绑定需要 root 或 `CAP_SYS_ADMIN` 权限。请以适当权限运行工作进程，或禁用 IRQ 绑定。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:156
msgid ""
"**Insufficient CPUs**: If the CPU pool is too small, the allocator will "
"log a warning and skip binding. Increase the available CPUs or reduce the"
" number of workers."
msgstr ""
"**CPU 不足**：如果 CPU 池太小，分配器将记录警告并跳过绑定。请增加可用 CPU 或减少工作进程数量。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:157
msgid ""
"**Binding not effective**: Verify that the system cpuset allows the "
"assigned CPUs. Use `taskset -p <pid>` to check the actual CPU affinity of"
" the worker process."
msgstr ""
"**绑定未生效**：验证系统 cpuset 是否允许分配的 CPU。使用 `taskset -p <pid>` 检查工作进程的实际 CPU 亲和性。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:158
msgid ""
"**Performance degradation**: If CPU binding causes performance issues, "
"try disabling it with `VLLM_ASCEND_CPU_BINDING=0` and compare "
"performance."
msgstr ""
"**性能下降**：如果 CPU 绑定导致性能问题，请尝试使用 `VLLM_ASCEND_CPU_BINDING=0` 禁用它并比较性能。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:160
msgid ""
"For more details, refer to the vllm-ascend documentation or open an issue"
" on the GitHub repository."
msgstr ""
"有关更多详细信息，请参阅 vllm-ascend 文档或在 GitHub 仓库中提交问题。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:93
msgid ""
"`topo_affinity` is designed for A2, Atlas 300 inference products, and "
"other non-A3 device types. A2 and Atlas 300 inference products expose "
"**meaningful NPU-to-CPU affinity information**, so the allocator starts "
"from NPU topology affinity when it is available and then avoids overlap "
"for shared affinity groups."
msgstr ""
"`topo_affinity`专为A2、Atlas 300推理产品及其他非A3设备类型设计。A2和Atlas 300"
"推理产品暴露了**有意义的NPU到CPU亲和性信息**，因此分配器在可用时从NPU拓扑亲和性开始，然后避免共享亲和性组的重叠。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:99
msgid "Build candidate NPUs from all logical NPUs:"
msgstr "从所有逻辑NPU构建候选NPU："

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:100
msgid "always include running NPUs"
msgstr "始终包含运行中的NPU"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:101
msgid ""
"include non-running NPUs only when their affinity overlaps this process's"
" allowed cpuset"
msgstr "仅当非运行中NPU的亲和性与该进程的允许cpuset重叠时才包含它们"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:102
msgid "For each candidate NPU, intersect topo affinity with `allowed_cpus`."
msgstr "对于每个候选NPU，将拓扑亲和性与`allowed_cpus`取交集。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:103
msgid "If the intersection is empty for a candidate, binding fails for this rank."
msgstr "如果某个候选NPU的交集为空，则此rank的绑定失败。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:104
msgid ""
"If the affinity CPUs are all on one NUMA node, extend the pool with CPUs "
"from the next NUMA node, constrained by `allowed_cpus`."
msgstr "如果亲和性CPU都在一个NUMA节点上，则使用来自下一个NUMA节点的CPU扩展池，受`allowed_cpus`约束。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:105
msgid ""
"Group NPUs with identical extended pools and split each shared pool "
"evenly across that group."
msgstr "将具有相同扩展池的NPU分组，并在该组内均匀分割每个共享池。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:106
msgid "Keep only running NPUs in the final `npu_cpu_pool`."
msgstr "在最终的`npu_cpu_pool`中仅保留运行中的NPU。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:108
msgid ""
"The non-running candidate step is intentional. It prevents two "
"independent single-card workers from selecting the same CPU range when "
"their visible NPUs share the same topology affinity."
msgstr "非运行候选步骤是有意设计的。它防止两个独立的单卡工作进程在它们可见的NPU共享相同拓扑亲和性时选择相同的CPU范围。"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:112
msgid "Role Split"
msgstr "角色拆分"

#: ../../source/developer_guide/Design_Documents/cpu_binding.md:114
msgid "After a CPU pool is built, the allocator splits it by role:"
msgstr "构建CPU池后，分配器按角色进行拆分："

